    • Method Detail

      • isExtendDefaults

        public boolean isExtendDefaults()
        This method determines if the internal default types shall be extended, when configuring SearchEntryTypes. In this case existing types are replaced if overridden. This is the default. If you want to reduce the number of types, you need to set this to false and define only the types, you like to have.
        NOTE:
        This method is only available in the API to document the configuration. It has no benefit for the end-user of the API.
        Specified by:
        isExtendDefaults in interface SearchEntryTypeContainer
        Returns:
        true to extend the defaults, false otherwise.

        public SearchEntryType getEntryType(String id)
        This method gets the SearchEntryType with the given ID.
        Specified by:
        getEntryType in interface SearchEntryTypeContainer
        Parameters:
        id - is the ID of the requested SearchEntryType.
        Returns:
        the SearchEntryType for the given id. If no such SearchEntryType exists the SearchEntryType with ID SearchEntryType.ID_ANY is returned. This has to be defined in a legal configuration.
